The paper deals with capacity analysis of wireless relay networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) concepts. The algorithmic approach used in the paper involves graph traversal and path augmentation, which are common techniques in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the algorithm, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper proposes a capacity-achieving transmission strategy, which can be considered as a system-level approach and falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SI).
